the central funicular (italian: funicolare centrale), is a funicular railway line that forms part of the public transport system for the city of naples, italy. opened in 1928, the central funicular of naples is one of the most used funicular railways in the world, and carries over 10 million passengers per year. central funicular connects four stations: piazza fuga, petraio-via palizzi, corso vittorio emanuele (napoli), and augusteo at piazzetta duca d'aosta. at piazza fuga, the central funicular station is adjacent to piazza vanvitelli, where there is a connection to both vanvitelli station, on line 1 of the naples metro, and to the chiaia funicular.